column1: Will Apple's end-of-day closing market capitalization reach or exceed $3 trillion before 31 December 2022?

Stocks on the downward and the price of raw materials on the downward. These, to me, are positive correlates to consider and therefore make it less likely as we continue to move away from the $3T threshold and observe "lackluster" movements resulting from the new iPhone announcement and its release this month.

Not going to happen.
The worsening economic outlook makes it harder and harder to see the market cap reaching 3T by year end. Where is the froth going to come from in the next three months?

I presume market caps tend to increase during times of inflation and economic trouble? This presumption made me jump up to 34% even though one lens I viewed this problem with pointed me toward a 17 to 25% probability.

Since my last prediction the price has dropped from $172 to $150, so the market cap is now ~$2.4T and it needs a 25% increase by EOY to get to $3T. This still seems possible but I'm going below 50% as it would require a significant rally in the market in the next 4 months.

The iPhone 14 has really good pre-sale numbers. However, the last time apple released a phone, their stock grew around 14% if my Googling is to be trusted. At today's evaluation, that would mean if Apple saw another 14% increase, they would only be around $2.7 trillion in market cap. Now with the economy going bad, it will probably be harder to rally stock. Unless the iPhone 14 has a huge numbers or an economic event happens, still probably unlikely.

General reasoning:Earnings and the multiple that Wall Street is willing to pay for those earnings are likely to decline as dollar strength, weak economies in China & Europe, and a weakening economy in the US all weigh on demand in 2H 2022Recent positives:Strong demand for iPhone 14Recent negatives:Monetary policy to remain a headwind to stock prices following 09/13 CPI dataMixed:Tech is among the most under-weighted or shorted of sectors.
General reasoning:
Bond yields should continue to rise and the US EQ beta will come down slightly. Odds are low that apple adds 25% of market cap in three volatile months.

I had a 1 in 5 chance that something spectacular would be announced at the Sept 7th event. Because it did not happen, I must take 20 percentage points off my odds. Recent price movements take another couple points off. Passage of time takes off one more. There are now 80 trading days left, and a rise of 20% would be required here.
Tepid market reaction following the product launch.

All Apple needs is a one day price increase of less than 20% in the period September - December. Factors: strong release of new products in September; Chinese market performing stable to good; general market exuberance resulting from strong market performance at 9/30/22, better than estimated q3 earnings across the board. Combined, these could result in an intraday 3T total cap valuation, as happened in January 2022.

17.5% rise needed now with 85 trading days left, so adjusting down some more. If I was 55% when a 8.7% rise was needed with 92 trading days (shots on goal) left, logically I should be lower than that when the hurdle is higher. As Marc Andreessen puts it, aim for "Strong beliefs, loosely held."
Tech overvaluation is trending down - supported by increasing interest rates and slowing consumer speding!
There is a potential anti-trust lawsuit brewing, however, if the iPhone 14 looks amazing and gets great reviews, then there could be a lot of upside for Apple.
Inflation is still high, so interest rates will continue to be raised until it drops.

Dropped to 2.63t. Economic indicators (inflation, interest rate trajectory) are still strongly not in favour of a 14% price increase, topping the highest ever closing valuation of the company, by the end of the year.
A lot will depend on Apple's upcoming new product event on Sept 7.
Calculated daily VAR, converted it to account for the ~80 trading days left in 2022.
Very roughly there are 92 trading days left in the year. So we need an 11.5% increase in share price vs Aug 22 close.
An 11.4% rise is now needed, so adjusting down slightly

This seems exceptionally likely given inflation, the recent trend of the stock and the fact that is only needs to bounce by ~9% to get there. It seems like it could almost get there on volatility alone, and since the question only requires it to get there one day, not to hold that until the end of the year, I'm pretty confident in it.

Currently 2.76t, so needs to go up about 10% within 4.5 months. Not implausible, but highly unlikely. Rising interest rates will likely be a drag on market cap growth due to their effect on the value of future earnings and the risk of a recession. Hard to see the trigger for 10% increase in market cap in the time available. Would take Apple into the peak territory it was in when markets were ridiculously overvalued, before inflation and interests rates became a concern. Only sensational earnings results or a market rattling product/acquisition announcement might do the trick.
